title: Interrupted Codex turn leaves hark ask blocked in audio capture
updated_at: "2026-07-15T23:43:03Z"
---
A bound 'hark ask --confirm never' outlived an interrupted Codex turn and remained blocked indefinitely in PortAudio Pa_ReadStream with no further transcript or timeout progress. Recovery required sending Ctrl-C to the original PTY session. Hark then emitted a full KeyboardInterrupt traceback from capture_utterance instead of a clean cancelled result. The unified monitor survived but 'hark start --status' showed workers not running. Hark should handle orchestrator/process interruption gracefully, release capture, return a structured cancellation, and avoid a raw traceback.